<br>
- While medding, you are not killing/pulling mobs, and not getting experience<br>
- You are very vulnerable after a rough fight, when mana and pet health are low<br>
<br>
As long as you have a decent group and the pulls are constant, you will do better than going out for the big game you are capable of handling solo. One of the things I love about my mage is that I can solo when I want to (usually if play time is limited) or have to (no groups to be had). This is something I did not/do not have as my enchanter (yes soloing is possible, but risky).<br>
<br>
Blackburrow has a definite path that trains get pulled along. If trains from other people are what is making you zone often, have your group pull to a different spot. If your group is causing the trains, then work out better tactics or recruit a stronger group. Runner control is extremely important here -- if you have a druid, ranger, necromancer, or shadowknight in your party, then snare/darkness will handle this well. If you don't have any of these, then you can use the earth pet with the knowledge that you WILL take some extra pounding (as root negates flee mode and the mobs will fight to the death).<br>
<br>
And as Nab said, Everfrost is pretty good hunting. If you want the best of both worlds, talk your party into going there. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Probably the best solution is to solo some and group some, so you get the best feel for your capabilities (which is good to do no matter what class you play). <p><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

